Pretty soon you may be able to find out your political party's most loyal donor. Public hearings are being held, and their looking into into the Political Party Funding Act's regulations. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The IEC is determined to have the Political Party Funding Bill enforced by the next local government elections. The act was signed into law in January, but regulations for its implementation still need to be determined. The electoral body held the first of its two-day public hearings on Thursday on the matter. READ: Group calls for political funding transparency Lobby groups say voters have the right to know before they cast their ballots but they are still concerned about anonymous donors. Trade union federation Cosatu wants all donations to political parties, no matter how small, to be declared. eNCA reporter Lindsay Dentlinger has more details in the video above.